Tuolumne River Instream Flow to Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the Weighted Usable Area (WUA) in square feet per 1000 feet as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

tuolumne_river_instream

Format

dataframe with 30 rows and 4 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_spawn_wua

chinook spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_fry_wua

chinook fry (up to 50 mm) WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

FR_juv_wua

chinook juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_spawn_WUA

steelhead spawning WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_fry_WUA

steelhead fry (up to 50 mm) WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

ST_juv_WUA

steelhead juvenile WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

adult_ST_WUA

adult steelhead WUA in square feet per 1000 feet

watershed

name of watershed

Source

Flo2D model by Stillwater, 2014

Details

The spawning and rearing WUAs were derived using a PHABSIM model by Stillwater 2010.
